Tammy Petersen, News24Cape Town - The 23-year-old man who was taken in for questioning in connection with the murder of 11-year-old Shamonique Claasen has been arrested, Western Cape police said.Captain FC Van Wyk confirmed that the suspect, believed to be a relative, was to appear in the Paarl Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Thursday after being charged.Claasen was found under a bed, wrapped in a blanket, on Monday evening.Her mother reported her missing at the Paarl East police station on Sunday. Police and her relatives had failed to find her during a search that day.A family member "picked up a smell" in their home the next day and found her body.A post mortem would be conducted to determine the cause of death.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.